4.7.3 Curvature Estimation

To estimate the curvature, we take a slice through the optimal point in the direction of the gradient of $I_{3322}$. Along this slice, we compute the boundary of $\mathcal{Q}^{(2)}$ by solving the SDP for fixed $I_{3322}$ values slightly above and below the optimum. The second derivative of the boundary curve gives the curvature:

\kappa = \frac{|f''(t)|}{(1 + f'(t)^2)^{3/2}} \approx 0.12,

where $f(t)$ parametrises the boundary in the slice. The dimension of $\Gamma^{(2)}$ is $n = 22$, so $1/n \approx 0.045$. The ratio $\kappa / (1/n) \approx 2.7$, consistent with the scaling conjecture.

